23 (32) Develop a statewide policy to promote employee and faculty development in state
24 and locally operated secondary area technology centers through the waiver of
25 tuition for college credit coursework in the public postsecondary education system.
26 Any regular full-time employee of a state or locally operated secondary area
27 technology center may, with prior administrative approval of the course offering
